&lt;span class="ne"&gt;ValueError&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;unknown&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;locale&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;UTF&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="mi"&gt;8&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;h2&gt;ValueError: unknown locale: UTF-8&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We get a &lt;code&gt;ValueError&lt;/code&gt;, Now the solution of this is proposed in one Stackoverflow Question &lt;a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/19961239/pelican-3-3-pelican-quickstart-error-valueerror-unknown-locale-utf-8"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have to add these two line in our bashrc file.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;export LC_ALL=en_US.UTF-8
export LANG=en_US.UTF-8
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Once we add this line, we can again issue the &lt;code&gt;pelican-quickstart&lt;/code&gt; command to get to the 10 question.&lt;/p&gt;</summary></entry><entry><title>Pelican Installation</title><link href="http://archerimagine.github.io/pelicanInstallation.html" rel="alternate"></link><updated>2015-07-09T00:00:00+05:30</updated><author><name>Archer Imagine</name></author><id>tag:archerimagine.github.io,2015-07-09:pelicanInstallation.html</id><summary type="html">&lt;h1&gt;Install Pelican.&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will start with a short guide to install pelican on to your system.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you use &lt;code&gt;pip&lt;/code&gt; installation is very simple.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;pip install pelican
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;h2&gt;Markdown Support&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you write your blog with Markdown format, you need an additional plugin called &lt;code&gt;markdown&lt;/code&gt;, you can again install it using &lt;code&gt;pip&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;pip install markdown
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;h2&gt;Additional ways&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can also use &lt;a href="http://www.virtualenv.org/"&gt;virtualenv&lt;/a&gt; to install pelican.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;References&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Some links which will help you in this regards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="http://docs.getpelican.com/en/latest/install.html"&gt;Pelican Docs&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
